item.title: About Me
item.dc:creator: sandrag
item.content:encoded:
Hey Everybody,

My name is Sandra Gannon. I'm 21 years old and a third year student studying Creative Digital Media in the Institute of Technology Blanchardstown. I have a keen interest in brand design and graphic design. I've skills in many different softwares including Adobe illustrator, Adobe Indesign, Photoshop and Dreamweaver. I have also studied in Rathmines College for one year just after completing my Leaving Certificate. During my time at Rathmines I studied Journalism and P.R. After studying this I knew I wanted to stay in Media, then I applied for ITB.  

This portfolio is to display all my work I have created here at my time at ITB.  I'm currently looking for work experience in Graphic Design company, my work experience begins early February of next year.

In the future I hope to work as a graphic designer. Have a look around my portfolio and get me know me a bit better!

 

 

Feel free to check out my other site and my downloadable CV!

 

 

Check out my photography

Check out my second cms site!

item.content:encoded:
Some of my Designs

 

three-different-logo-ideas
This is a brand design assignment where I had to create a logo for a company called 'Wellclik'. Wellclik is an app where you can book appointments, I created this logo with the guidance from a live client to help their vision come to life.

 

 

print-business-card

The business card I created using the logo for 'Wellclik'. I made it simple and effective.

 

 

 

 

 

lab3

This a lab which in I created a logo for the word 'KICK' but it had to relate to the word.

mickeymouse

This a design of the popular disney character Mickey Mouse, I created this by using adobe illustrator and putting all different words relating to Mickey Mouse inside the character giving it the effect that it is just words and not an image.

 

 

 

 

tommy-the-tutle

I created Tommy the Turtle in Adobe Illustrator using the pen tool.

 

I recreated John Lennon using Typography, this was created in Photoshop.

 

This was a product shot taken for an photography assignment edited using Photoshop.
